Instructions for other Unixes
-----------------------------

FreeBSD 8.4
-----------

Required packages: qt4-gui (4.8.4), qt4-moc (4.8.4), qt4-network (4.8.4),
                   qt4-designer (4.8.4), qt4-rcc (4.8.4), qt4-uic (4.8.4),
                   qt4-qmake (4.8.4), qt4-linguist (4.8.4)

OpenSSL is part of the system libraries.

FreeBSD 9.1
-----------

Required packages: qt4-gui (4.7.4), qt4-moc (4.7.4), qt4-network (4.7.4),
                   qt4-designer (4.7.4), qt4-rcc (4.7.4), qt4-uic (4.7.4),
                   qt4-qmake (4.7.4), qt4-linguist (4.8.4)

OpenSSL is part of the system libraries.

Qt misses some I18N programs on 32-bit, so you can't build the wolfclient
there.

You need 'gmake' (3.82).

NetBSD 6.1
----------

Required packages: qt4 (4.8.4nb5)

You also need 'gmake' (3.82nb7).

Make sure '/usr/pkg/qt4/bin' and '/usr/pkg/bin' are part of the path.
Also set 'QTDIR' to '/usr/pkg/qt4'.

Build with:

qmake -config debug -recursive

Apply a patch for libtool for all generated makefiles

find . -name Makefile -exec sh -c \
	"sed 's/libtool --silent/libtool --silent --tag=CXX/g' {} > x && mv x {}" \;

Build with

gmake

When you run the libtool wrapper scripts, make sure LD_LIBRARY_PATH is set to /usr/X11R7/lib

